title: r/Choosingbeggars "You Want Me To PAY For The Product? WTF?"
description: r/Choosingbeggars In today's episode, OP is trying to sell an old computer for a mere $2 bucks. What could possibly be wrong with such an incredible deal? Is the choosing beggar upset that the computer is too expensive? No -- the opposite! The choosing beggar expects OP to give the choosing beggar money to come take the computer. This choosing beggar literally believes that free is too expensive!
